dc_title_s: Clayton County, Iowa, 1940, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet labels. Images are photoreductions of mosaics created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol FR. Form of individual image numbering: FR-1A-[number], FR-2A-[number], FR-5A-[number], FR-6A-[number], or FR-7A-[number]. "Flying completed 10-9-40." Flown by Aero Service Corp. Philidelphia, Pa. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
dc_publisher_s: United States. Department of Agriculture|United States. Agricultural Stabilization and Conservation Service
